.\" Man page for lob-encode
.TH LOB-ENCODE 1 "April 2026" "libobsh 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
lob-encode \- Convert a file to a Library of Babel coordinate
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B lob-encode
.I file
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B lob-encode
reads a file and converts it to a deterministic Library of Babel
coordinate. The coordinate is saved as a \fI.coord\fR file.
.PP
If the file is larger than 3200 bytes, it is automatically split
into pages; a manifest is stored in the Library, and the manifest
coordinate is saved as the \fI.coord\fR file. The decoder can
reconstruct the original file from this single coordinate.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B lob-encode script.sh
Creates \fIscript.sh.coord\fR.
.SH FILES
.I file.coord
Output coordinate file.
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.BR lob-decode (1),
.BR lob-run (1)
